r excludes test classes, but the dynamic access report tracks during native test compilation—not the agent. I need to dig deeper into this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering parser integration**\\n\\nI’m noting that the Oracle parser is absent, and I wonder if I could add a test dependency. But then again, I think I might need to create a parser that actually converts the input into a DOM Document using JAXP. It looks like the relevant classes are in oracle.xml.parser. They provide methods like `parse(InputSource)` and `getDocument`. I need to figure out how to integrate this with the InputSource from the stream.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rI6ofsCuUJpNogXwX364Qpae|fc_08b252f149c2e0d60169ef8cf07510819ca32cd38b40af4ecd", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0/src/test/java/jdom/jdom/OracleV1DOMAdapterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage jdom.jdom;\n\nimport org.jdom.adapters.OracleV1DOMAdapter;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Document;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Element;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class OracleV1DOMAdapterTest {\n    @Test\n    void getDocumentParsesInputThroughOracleParserAdapter() throws Exception {\n        OracleV1DOMAdapter adapter = new OracleV1DOMAdapter();\n        String xml = \"\"\"\n                <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n                <oracle:root xmlns:oracle=\"urn:jdom-oracle-adapter\">\n                  <oracle:child name=\"parsed\">text</oracle:child>\n                </oracle:root>\n                \"\"\";\n\n        Document document = adapter.getDocument(new ByteArrayInputStream(xml.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8)), false);\n        Element root = document.getDocumentElement();\n        Element child = (Element) root.getElementsByTagNameNS(\"urn:jdom-oracle-adapter\", \"child\").item(0);\n\n        assertThat(root.getNamespaceURI()).isEqualTo(\"urn:jdom-oracle-adapter\");\n        assertThat(root.getLocalName()).isEqualTo(\"root\");\n        assertThat(child.getAttribute(\"name\")).isEqualTo(\"parsed\");\n        assertThat(child.getTextContent()).isEqualTo(\"text\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3211, "output": 1487, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28250, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777306845567, "responseId": "resp_08b252f149c2e0d60169ef8cde6780819c83d0c1b262fb187a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_rI6ofsCuUJpNogXwX364Qpae|fc_08b252f149c2e0d60169ef8cf07510819ca32cd38b40af4ecd", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1518 bytes to tests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0/src/test/java/jdom/jdom/OracleV1DOMAdapterTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777306866189}]}
